President Biden and President Fernández of Argentina met in the Oval Office to discuss their countries' diplomatic relations and opportunities for cooperation. They expressed their commitment to democracy, human rights, and addressing global challenges such as the COVID-19 pandemic, economic problems, the Russian invasion of Ukraine, and climate change. President Fernández thanked President Biden for his support, including the supply of vaccines to Argentina. He also expressed solidarity with the victims of the Nashville tragedy and supported President Biden's initiative to regulate the sale of firearms in the United States. President Biden expressed gratitude for the support and sympathy and mentioned that his wife was meeting with the families of the victims. He also learned that Pope Francis was in the hospital and expressed concern, as they are good friends.